W: Verse 2.
W: But where is my love gone with his cheeks like roses?
W: He’s gone across the sea gathering primroses.
W: I’m afraid the scorching sun will shine and burn his beauty,
W: And if I was with my love I’d do my duty.
W: Verse 3.
W: Strange news is come to town, strange news is carried.
W: Strange news flies up and down that my love is married.
W: I wish them both much joy although they cannot hear me.
W: And may God reward him well for the slighting of me.
W: Verse 4.
W: Don’t you remember when you lay beside me?
W: And you said you’d marry me and not deny me?
W: If I said I’d marry you it was only for to try you,
W: So bring your witness love and I’ll not deny you.
W: Verse 5
W: No, witness have I none save God Almighty,
W: And may he reward you well for the slighting of me.
W: Her cheeks grew pale and wan it made her poor heart tremble,
W: To think she loved that one and he proved deceitful. (BA) | "Em" G2 y E2 y G2 (AB) | "D" d6 (AB) | "CM7" B3 y E "D" y D2 E2- | "Em" E6 (BA) |

W:2. In a field down by the river
W:My love and I did stand
W:And upon my leaning shoulder
W:She laid her snow-white hand
W:She bid me take life easy
W:As the grass grows on the weirs
W:But I was young and foolish
W:And now I am full of tears

W:She crossed the Sally gardens
W:With little snow-white feet
W:She bid me to take life easy
W:As the leaves grow on the tree

W: Francis O’Neill got this reel from Jeremiah O’Reilly, hence the title 
W: 'O’Reilly’s Greyhound.' 
W: 
W: Breandan Breathnach published it as 'Murphy’s Greyhound.' It dates back to 1903.
W: 
W: It was first recorded by William Mullaly in 1927 on the cylinder titled
W: 'The Westmeath Hunt'. William Mullaly (concertina).
W:
W: Book: As tune #1488 in [1850] 'O'Neill's Music of Ireland' by Francis O'Neill and 
W: James O'Neill. |: eA~A2 EAce | dBGB A~E3 | eA~A2 EAce | ageB dega |
eA~A2 EAce | dBGB A~E3 | DEGA B2ge | dBGA BAA2 :|
|: eaag aged | BddA BA~A2 | eaab aged | BAGE DEG2 |
eaag aged | BddA BA~A2 | efge a2ge | dBGA BAA2 :| |: eA A2 EAce | dBGB AE E2 | eA A2 EAce | aged (3Bcd ga |
